main event: On 28 July 1954, an observer on duty at Bolling Air Force Base, Washington D.C., reported seeing two brightly lighted objects hovering over the College Park area of Maryland.
interesting points: The lower object was much brighter than the upper object,The observation was made at 2310 hours,The observer's camera malfunctioned preventing further documentation,The objects appeared to be larger and lower than any stars observed that night,One object disappeared while the other moved rapidly and gradually became smaller.
witness description: Air Force personnel on duty at control tower
